title: SF Fed chief Williams says short-term rate should go up this year
text:
Photo: Scott Strazzante / Scott Strazzante / The Chronicle San Francisco Federal Reserve President John Williams speaks at the Urban Land Institute meeting in San Francisco on Tuesday. San Francisco Federal Reserve President John Williams speaks at the...
With the labor market nearing full employment, the “next appropriate step” for the Fed is to start raising short-term interest rates sometime this year, San Francisco Federal Reserve chief John Williams said during a speech in San Francisco Tuesday.
